title: Texas nationalists cheer Catalonia independence referendum
description:
Following Catalonia’s independence vote on Sunday, nationalists in the US are promoting the referendum as a model for the state of Texas. A portion of the Lone Star state’s population has long advocated for secession from the US, and with the recent votes in Scotland and Spain, some are increasingly calling a referendum of their own. RT’s Manila Chan discusses with Daniel Miller, president of the Texas Nationalist Movement.
